<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-1C81032B-89AA-4C1B-AD5D-045C3DC3F689" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-1C81032B-89AA-4C1B-AD5D-045C3DC3F689" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">01 The process of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> drives the UV curing lamps (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pre curing lamp PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 01PBA01 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">PRE_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp> and <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Pin Post Cure lamp PBA (UV LED lamp 75/50)</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 01PBA02 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">POST_PIN_CURE_LAMP</compsignal></comp>) . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The input for the lamp control PBA comes from the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-FF5A854A-A922-4873-A4CA-4BE4145102C3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> controls the following curing aspects: 
</p><ul id="UL_1DBF8E5243764FB09ACD4A8F1DEB5755" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_62815429DAFB4D9CA028EB6B417B6F90" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Enable / disable the curing lamps. 
</p></li><li id="LI_A58AD43FF4EC45D59806F06C7085ACDE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Control the intensity (power) of the curing lamps. 
</p></li><li id="LI_8343C5BAFD514074BD7FB2AD81D40FAB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the lamps are switched ON/OFF. 
</p></li><li id="LI_E7B1D22ADC3943F8B95AD37C2DD98211" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Monitor the temperature of the curing lamps. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Block diagram</title><fig id="FIG_66807E3E494F4A7294133A1F31DCAEEA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D01E577C-7F27-42FE-B5A1-A860D960A31E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D01E577C-7F27-42FE-B5A1-A860D960A31E-low.png"/></fig><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lamp 1: Pre curing lamp 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lamp 2: Post curing lamp and Pin curing lamp 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Controller part uses the control signals to drive and check the curing lamps. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The control signals come from the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The SLM (Semiconductor Light Matrix) drivers drive the curing lamps. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The power is received from <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-69D9B90C-7016-4928-988E-2792FC2F6F8C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Enhanced block diagram</title><fig id="GUID-3C013CA4-4042-493C-AFEB-93A1E6CF325B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C8AA5B5E-4394-4BB2-850D-AC440AD819B8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C8AA5B5E-4394-4BB2-850D-AC440AD819B8-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Explanation : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A + A 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The connections to both pre - and post curing lamps. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Carries control signals and power. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">B + C</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> RS-485 interface and other control signals from the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">IOBOARD_BE PBA </compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 21PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">D</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Supply power for driving the lamps. The power is received from <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">48 VDC Supply Curing</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22G04 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">48V_CUR/1</compsignal></comp> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">E</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Only used for R&amp;D purposes. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">F</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Vref indicates that power is present on the PBA. 
</p></li></ul></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B6F5A54C-52D7-45D2-9AE2-815392CF0F57.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
